<lj-cut text="69 Questions to Start the Summer">

1. Are you in a relationship?
No

2. Do you hate more than 3 people?
No sir. But there is this boy at work who puts me in a bad mood most days.

3. How many houses have you lived in?
I have one home. I've lived in three houses. Four with the apartment.

4. What is your favorite candy bar?
Just chocolate mostly. I don't eat candy bars much.

5. What are your favorite shoes?
My mom has these shoes that are light olive green. They have tinytiny heels and just cover the front part of the foot with little eyelets in them. I do love the flowered wedges...and the mocassin-like wedges.

6. Have you ever tripped someone?
I have. One time Kendra tripped me and I fell on the ground in 8th grade. I try to get her still, but I'm not so good at it.

7. What was your least favorite subject this year?
I love all my teachers this year, but Pre-Cal was very frustrating academically.

8. What was your favorite subject this year?
Art was great because I love Mrs. Parker, but Sculpture was totally new.

9. Do you own a Britney Spears CD?
Two. One? Two.

10. Have you ever thrown up in public?
Ya man. I did at work two months ago...and Mark G. walked in and it was super green. I felt bad for him. Then I had to clean it up.

11. Name something that's always on your mind.
Art.Music.Travel.

12. What is your favorite music genre?
I think it would be shameful to pick just one. It totally depends on the mood...but usually chill.meaningful stuff.

13. whats your zodiac sign?
Taurus.

14. What time were you born?
One AM.

15. Do you like beer?
I did when I was little, but I do not enjoy it now at all.

16. Have you ever made a prank call?
I have. Yes. Quite a few good ones in Kendra's presence. Quite immature.

17. What is the most embarrassing CD you own?
I honestly don't remember many of the CDs I own. I'm not embarassed by any of them too much...but I suppose some would consider NSYNC to be slightly embarassing. 

18. Are you sarcastic?
Not usually lately...that I've noticed.

19. What are your favorite colors?
I love olive citrus green. Mellow yellow and mocha brown. Certain shades of blue that are light and turqouisey and the occasional shade of pumpkin or beige.

20. How many watches do you own?
Zero.

21. Summer or winter?
Mmm. Usually winter...but right now I have the jonesins for some warmth.

22. Spring or fall?
Fall

23. What is your favorite color to wear?
Green.

24. Pepsi or Sprite?
Sprite.

25. What color is your cell phone?
Silver and black.

26. Where is your second home?
Mmm. My car.

27. Have you ever slapped someone?
I might have dreamed it. It seems familiar but I can't place it.

28. Have you ever had a cavity?
Yes. I got four all at once. Ever since then I'm quite paranoid about it...but I haven't had one since.

29. How many lamps are in your bedroom?
One. It's a very dimly lit room.

30. How many video games do you own?
Both of The Sims plus various expansion packs...and Roller Coaster Tycoon 2. 

31. What was your first pet?
Blackie the rabbit. And Spot. They had babies together and I dropped Blackie's look-alike son. He died.

32. Have you ever had braces?
Yes. 

33. Do looks matter?
Looks attract more easily...but it doesn't hold fast.

34. Do you use chapstick?
Yes.

35. Name 3 teachers from your high school.
Parker Brazill Rozewski

36. American Eagle or Abercrombie?
American Eagle?

37. Are you too forgiving?
I don't know if that's possible.

38. How many children do you want?
I think any number would be nice. One to have a special bond with. Two.three.four.

39. Do you own something from Hot Topic?
I do.

40. What is your favorite breakfast?
Pie and ice cream.

41. Do you own a gun?
M hm.

42. Have you ever thought you were in love?
I've been in love with ideas and intense awe and amazement of some people. I've loveloved and lovelove many people. But I don't know if I've ever come to the conclusion that I was in love with someone.

43. When was the last time you cried?
For Jeremy Machado last week.

44. What did you do 3 nights ago?
I was at Cold Stone eating a Cake Batter and Brownie ice cream.

45. When was the last time you went to Olive Garden?
For my mother's birthday two years ago.

46. Have you ever called your teacher mom?
Once when I was little. She didn't hear me.

47. Have you ever been in a castle?
No.

48. What are your nicknames?
Uh. Mol.

49. Do you know anyone named Bertha?
At church.

50. Have you ever been to Kentucky?
No.

51. Do you own something from Banana Republic?
I do.

52. Are you thinking about somebody right now?
I'm thinking about this survey right now.

53. Have you ever called someone Boo?
No sir. I'm not fond of the term. It reminds me of a bad hip hop video.

54. Do you smoke?
I have.

55. Do you own a diamond ring?
Yes. Two I think.

56. Are you happy with your life right now?
I'm satisfied but not overjoyed. There are hopeful things in the future binding it together.

57. Do you dye your hair?
I dyed it brown a few months ago.

58. Does anyone like you?
Not that I'm certain of.

59. Do you like anyone?
I'm not sure.

60. What were you doing May of 1994.
Starting my first year of swim team. And eating dirt cake for my brothers 7th birthday.

61. Do you own a Backstreet Boys CD?
Black&Blue

62. McDonald's or Wendy's?
Wendy's

63. Do you like yourself?
I'm content sometimes. I get very frustrated with shortcomings and struggles and rejections but what can you do?

64. Are you closer to your mother or father?
My mum. But I love my Dad's secret vulnerabilitiy and quirks.

65. Favorite body feature of the opposite sex?
Chest and upper stomach.fingers.lips and hips.

66. Are you afraid of the dark?
I used to be terrified. But I find it quite relaxing now.

67. Have you ever eaten paste?
Tomato paste.

68. Do you have a webcam?
I own one.

69. Have you ever stripped?
Yes. But not for sexual purposes.

Bloooooooooop'ajof;iuna;coidfush'nkf;.

I'm atrociously lazy updating with pictures. I suppose some would be nice.

On second thought, no one ever reads this, which makes this text strange to be typing.


Holler if you have any thoughts regarding future posting of semi-recent pictures that make me giggly or reminiscent or blahblah.

On Sunday, I worked with these 5 mostly obnoxious boys. We were setting up for a wedding and they were body slamming each other in between the tables. The lunch conversation migrated into strip clubs and bossman saying our homework was to get Phil wasted. Then I went to San Ramon to see Adam and we went to Target to get CDs. We proceeded to get a collection of some of his very interesting friends and Eli was pushing me to go fasterfaster in the 0 visibility pouring rain. We had puppy class on Monday and. I realized there weren't any pictures of Ches. This is my favorite guy.ever. Sleeping by the heater. Chance! He's the same size as Lola. Mm. This is the first night we had him. Aw. I love this one. At church. I snagged this fo sho. Uh! What it is. Bio table fo life. M. Me. Sunshine. Ma mere. And JenniferStupak!

Ah! Finally! I have reverted to last year and I am almost completely unbothered. It feels almost like it did when I was in Science and they kept coming in to our class with that stupid thing and I'm like. 'Uh...??? Lame?' I hate to be a NegativeNancy, but really. It's so intensely joyful to come to this realization, being freed and unblinded and unattached. 

Chesley was super today and I loveKendra.

Much love JenniferStupak. Come home soonish cause we need to roll fo sho.

---

On another note. Most everyone failed our Precal test, so we got to retake it. I didn't really feel like studying or doing anything, so I failed again. This semester is going to be tres difficule, so I might transfer out. I figured I could go to M&M but then I realized that class change would be atrocious. Kendra suggested TA'ing for her class. Killersauce.

AND I'M EMPLOYED. 17 DINERO AN HOUR. WOO.

Ah! I talked to ma grand-mere just now. She is the epitome of euphoria. And Adam. I love that kid...hilariousness. I suppose posts have been lacking in a major way, but I have some sample pictures I would fuhlove to share. (Johan?) Speaking of Johan. I have not seen that boy in. Over two years now. I'm sure he relates me to myself in 8th grade, which is atrocious and embarassing and I don't blame him. Kendra and I must go see Ariana as well. Samantha Smith. I love you. I wish you could come back fo sho. I totally miss you and I thought about you all day yesterday. Jacob.Skills. What does it look like? Ben is crazysauce wild man and then grabbed my face. ----- Johnny Rockets, yes? The enthusiasm. ----- Ha. Michelle. Dancing. And bleaching Amanda's hair. ----- Gracie in Dan's shirt. Matt holding Baby Baby. She's super. ----- Sunshine! Whoa. ----- Chris and I went to go shoot his rocket off at the park. He's not into pictures ----- Functionality! ----- Discovering the awesomeness of Honey Bunches of Oats with Almonds Jessica Stupak represent. The lighting on this bed was fantastic. JenniferStupak IKEA. "But zhee. If et iz lyk zees, we cannot accept." Eraserfire ----- Kendra birthday! Chris and Shannon. There is a fat series of these. Woo hoo for pants. And 4 gangsters in a car. ----- Nice. C'est faux. I like this guy. This road was deserted. Ya man. Horse craziness. Eh. And home. Reading rocks! Oh boy. And yesterday I was at my Dad's and Malee made awesomeawesome. food. Fish cakes with green beans and rice with peanut and cucumber and sweet sauce. I know what it sounds like. But wow.

Some of the most comfortable people, and my favorite ones are those who are appreciative, homely, comfortable and spontaneous. The small represents the big.

"If chickens only knew what they were in for, they'd stay in their egg."

3-1 to 2.

It is the early morning of the night of Kendra's birthday, so technically it was yesterday, but it's still today.

Happy birthday love! You're inexplicably awesome.

Is so wonderful. I'll let the pictures tell a story. This is our Christmas tree. Kendra and such on the way down. Woo! It was foggy. At a Taco Bell This is our 'Border Crossing' picture Scott Taco Stand Courtyard. Mexican! Awfully skinny dog. They renamed it Sadie. Zebra Gum Tongue Tattoos Kendra's hottieface sweater Kendra.Sunshine.Mexican. She's home! Marsha! This was so hilarious. One night Sunshine Kendra and I decided to sleep in this other building since our people were snoring. Marsha said it was totally cool and she didn't snore. Ten minutes later she's asleep and snoring so atrociously. Anyway. All you had to say was, "Marsha...shhhhhhh..." And she would stop instantly. It was joyous. Worksite Day Two Their other roof Jorge! This is Chris and Andy on the boards. Sunshine and Josh Elbar and Andy were totally cool. This is Veronico's despair after trying to nail this piece in for almost half an hour. This is the hottiest pose I've seen. I never got this boy's name. Jorge! Stuff Janky smiles for lunch. Jose was totally picking his nose but I took the picture too late. Like. Picking for a long time. We were up on the roof from 8-11 and then didn't touch the ground from after lunch to sundown. It was.good. Worksite Day Three Etc. Down the hill. This house was killer. We cut and nailed drywall like crazy. Precision is too important. Joel and Josh! Joel is super gangster and is from Cancun. He's in Tijuana for three months and says it's dirty and ugly. So. I was getting tired and it was towards the end of the day. Everyone went to go pass out food to some people but I didn't go for some reason. Anyway. I stick this up on the wall and I totally had cut the light switch hole on the other side. So I was like.fuck. But then I fixed it with putty as glue! Joel was happy. Later my Mom's Dave said when that happens you have to do something with the paper and make a bigger contact area. But whatev. Some inside. Veronico and Kendra on the roof. Neighbor's Kendra's nervousness in climbing down ladders. The porch! Jorge! Jorge and me. There was a lot of sheetrock dust in the air and the flash went off. This little boy was sick I think and drank water.andwater.andwater. Jesus Emmanuel! "Mi Churro" Ha. Jose. This little boy was fun. Jose never wanted pictures. But for some reason I was like. "Look! Look here and he totally did." I asked this boy his name three times but he was entirely soft-spoken and all I got was. Msheehdmshe...G something Martinez. So we will call him Mr. Martinez. Jesus is the cutiest. The Crew He totally started crying. But it was so fantastic. The Dad guy would slap their hand and they'd do this shakey wave thing to their other hand. It was great. Jorge and his friend. It was so great. All these kids started running in to the picture. And then Elbar ran out and had me come in. Then he took the camera. This is the Elbar series. Homeward. PS. The man at the grocery store asked me why I was cold. I think I was just frustrated with the chocolate bar that kept falling off the shelf. But he gave me a 'Life is Fantastic' sticker and said I should work there. What a fellow.

I just got back from Mexico with Kendralove and it was so fulfilling and wonderful. I finally got my Camp Campbell pictures back though, so I'm just going to post those for now so as not to overwhelm with too many photos. Woo. Edgar.Faisal.Michael and Victor Edgar had this huge pack of cutips he used all the time... And jumped into Jacob's picture. Marcos...hilarious Kenneth. Ha. This was on the way to Field Study and they were chasing me cause everyone was trying not to get a picture taken of them. And I ran ahead and snapped this over my head and then they tackled me. They're swell. Alex Edgar and Mrs. White I think this is the only picture of Declan's face. This girl looked so much like a little Nicole. She must have only weighed 50 pounds at the most. Michael and Faisal on the all-day hike Kenneth always smiles big for pictures. Edgar and me at the dining table. Michelle and I on Spider Mountain. Alex.Jacob.Michael.Faisal.Edgar.Victor.Marcos.Declan.Kenneth. Joseph and Arthur from our meal group. I love the kid on the left's face. They found out their beanies stuck to the walls so they would throw it up as high as they could. The highest points were always over Declan's bed and he would scream if you touched his bunk. On the way home...

1. What did you do in 2005 that you'd never done before?
Uhh. Cried repeatedly in public. 

2. Did you keep your new years' resolutions, and will you make more for next year?
I have never participated in that ritual.

3. Did anyone close to you give birth?
Not really. Some teachers I think.

4. Did anyone close to you die?
Pop Pop.

5. What countries did you visit?
None this year. Perhaps Mexico.

6. What would you like to have in 2006 that you lacked in 2005?
Yearlong, consistent happiness and painlessness.

7. What date from 2005 will remain etched upon your memory, and why?
September 30. 

8. What was your biggest achievement of the year?
License? But driving is weak.

9. What was your biggest failure?
Ruining my favorite relationship and not being able to sustain a good mood.

10. Did you suffer illness or injury?
I suppose.

11. What was the best thing you bought?
Oh boy. Bamboo floors? or some clothes?

12. Whose behavior merited celebration?
Amanda.Michelle.Amber.Shannon.Nicole.Danielle.Etc.etc.

13. Whose behavior made you appalled and depressed?
Obviously.

14. Where did most of your money go?
I honestly didn't have monay. Plane tickets and clothes.

15. What did you get really, really, really excited about?
Going to Connecticut. Coming home from Montana and seeing my friend.

16. What song will always remind you of 2005?
Ouch. I have no idea.

17. Compared to this time last year, are you:
i. happier or sadder? Sadder. And I was about to leave for New Orleans last year.
ii. thinner or fatter? Same I hope.
iii. richer or poorer? Same.

18. What do you wish you'd done more of?
Hugging.

19. What do you wish you'd done less of?
Seducing.

20. How will you be spending Christmas?
Rummaging through momentos of my great grandparents of Seattle.

22. Did you fall in love in 2005?
For sure. A couple times.

23. How many one-night stands?
Zero.

24. What were your favorite TV programs?
Six Feet Under. ANTM. Everwood. One Tree Hill. Gilmore Girls.

25. Do you hate anyone now that you didn't hate this time last year?
I can't accomplish hate. Would life be easier if I could?

26. What was the best book you read?
I read. One book. So The Bluest Eye.

27. What was your greatest musical discovery?
More Jason Mraz. Ben Folds for suuure. And Garden State soundtrack.

28. What did you want and got?
Hm. So many things but I'll just say a visit to the bathroom on a lake in Maine when in need.

30. What was your favorite film of this year?
Me And You And Everyone We Know. Ooncha!

31. What did you do on your birthday, and how old were you?
Went to Macaroni Grill with Kendra and my brothers and cousins. 16.

32. What one thing would have made your year immeasurably more satisfying?
Keeping my favorite friend of course. And you-know-who not doing heroin for good.

33. How would you describe your personal fashion concept in 2005?
Uh. Old lady and laid back and messy hair, which curls now. Aaand. Usually unfitted, and unfortunately often mid-revealing.

34. What kept you sane?
Uhhh. 

35. Which celebrity did you fancy the most?
Ouch. Rose Byrne in Wicker Park awed me. And Miranda July was incomprehensible.

36. What political issue stirred you the most?
I stopped caring.

37. Who did you miss?
My Grandma. DavidJohanSam

38. Who was the best new person you met?
Jennifer Stupak.Michelle Sanborn.

39. Tell us a valuable life lesson you learned in 2005:
Don't say you hate when you don't.

40. Quote a song lyric that sums up your year:
No songs. Just words.
It doesn't get easier. It just gets more familiar. -Billy.

Crying is gay. Especially when things set people off and they cry harder than they should from all the other things. And in front of kids? What a show. How atrocious.

In other news.
I went to Pastor Charlie's funeral today. Our church was overflowing and all the aisles were filled and people were standing and sitting on the sides and even into the entry area. Pastor Cork was there and I forgot how funny he was. Mrs. Poier asked me how The Used was. She's this tiny old lady who is so so nice and has this quiet, light, skipping voice. I'm a fan...and she said how her grandson is in a band in San Francisco and such. Then I drew cats in Pastor Tim's office for thrity minutes. Cats.cats.cats. 

But it was immensely grosso. On the freeway on the way home I was driving and I passed these Arab guys. And then they sped up and passed me and this like. Grosso.grosso. 50 year old Arab guy totally winked at me and I was like. 'Ew.' And totally slowed way down. How repulsive.

Mlehmlehmleh!

I finished my art journal, James, last night by doing 30 pages one after the other.

I feel so complete in that department right now. I got off my bed and looked at where I had been sitting...suitcase open. Light shining. Bed ruffled and supplies everywhere. It felt really good and now all 132 pieces and 200 pages are filled. Jooooyous.

Criteria:
*Bound.Not spiraled.
*At least the size of a composition book. No bigger than a regular sized paper.
*Blank paper.Preferrable off-white

Therapy is gangster. I was incomprehensibly bored last week. And took dancing shots. I have yet to dance in the street barefoot...but soon hopefully. Lately.lately.lately. Ummm. I think my Biology teacher smells like insulin and Christopher just made the most little kid noise ever. Like a breathy short laugh. How exciting. The Garden State soundtrack has changed my life. Or something close to it. I recommend you pick it up if you are able. Blahblah. No more news that I can think of. OH! The other day was most joyous. Jennifer Stupak and I both said we were going to have passionate love after Winter Ball...in unison.unplanned. And then with Danielle...we played soccer against three Mexicans in the hallway and won. Hector, Pedro and Joakie. They're now following Danielle. Then. Oh boy. I found twenty dollars on the ground in front of American Studies. At first I was going to try and find it's owner...but I realized it was almost impossible...so I gave it to Shannon in return for her being conned by the black man. And Amber Carney has given me the most wonderful small green flowered cloth. And Gabe gave me this comic strip about Ghandi. Some kids are super swell. They're only of me...so if that bothers you whatev. Some are fun...I thought... For some reason. This one totally makes me miss my grandmadre. Mm.A concert. Pour Amber Carney... Just because my hair has become curlyish. Good vibes to you.

Un image de ma grandmere et ses copains. 10 years ago.. I had this awesome teacher who had a twin. I got a pink card and had to stay in at recess for saying I couldn't understand the new Mexican girl. There was this kid Nam in my class whos Mom died and he was totally awesome. I remember him and Cathy both had Nguyen as last names. I spent five minutes making the & sign and I went up to show her and she says...'You have to write it out...'and' and erased it. I was mortified. At recess I lost my brand new earring underneath the sliding thing. I remember other kids would 'slam!' you and you had to try and catch it. On rainy days we ate in the cafeteria and you could buy pencils for a quarter. 5 years ago I hung out with Lauren and Heather even though they hated me and I didn't like them much either. I was pretty weaksauce. Mr. Alfonso had us draw things all the time. Self portraits.Shading cones.Pen on Paper. And we made TV shows and did trust walks. I don't remember doing work ever...except correcting spelling tests. We were the 'GAY' kids and we sat at the top of the Nature Center near the black top at lunch. 1 year ago... I loved Environmental Science most and I sat next to Hector and behind Rudy. Hector told me I could get a finger tattoo and the gangster kids wouldn't beat me up cause I was a little white girl. I hung out with Kendra and all her kids. I drank booze and I was actually pretty consistenly happy...except when I thought about my Grandma's death. I got my permit and...ya. Yesterday... I watched four hours of Six Feet Under when I woke up at one. Then I made banana pancakes and took out a zipper in one of my dresses. Later in the night I went to my Mom's friend Will's house and hung out with him...his son Zach and his grandma. I came home and Zarrinah was visiting and some guy named Jordan was there too. We stayed upstairs in Delilah's room till about 130 and they were dancing and telling jokes. They weren't themselves but it was funny. Zarrinah told me about her phone sex jobs...and then I took a shower and went to bed. 5 snacks I can't live without Almonds Rice cakes Triscuits Pineapple Chocolate 5 songs I know all the words to Blackalicious...Alphabet Aerobics Frank Sinatra...Days of Wine and Roses Spice Girls...Stop Snoop Dogg...Drop It Like It's Hot Ben Folds...Army 5 places I'd run away to Chok Chai 7327 52nd AVE NE Los Altos Chris's Thrift Store 5 things I'd never wear (Without feeling showy/funny) 80's Zubas Pants Old lady jeans Big Orange and black striped turtleneck Spice Girls platform shoes Cape 5 favorite TV shows... Six Feet Under One Tree Hill Everwood Gilmore Girls America's Next Top Model 5 of your favorite people... Grandma B Grandma M Kendra Samantha That one boy +My brother Dan +Adam +Madre +Ariana +Amber C is swell +Johan +Etc... 5 bad habits... Touching my lips Overly cautious about everything I eat Going to some people's sites Not doing my hair Sleeping? 5 of my biggest joys... Playing with Ben and Jacob Journals Music When people aren't critical and fully like...love. Authentic and original people +Dreaming 5 things I can't live without... iPod Art journal Drawing book Pens and paper Grandma's car 5 things I could do without... Whatever sickness I have Stoplight cameras Mean people Uncaring people Liarface/fake/disregarding people 5 people I tag to complete this... Ha. Like anyone will even see this.

Not only did I get to see Cory.Elise.Ben.andJacob today...but Abby and Jenn. This means nothing to anyone but me. And after painting our mural...my gangster cousins and I danced jigs and took some pickchas. I don't even care what they look like. They totally make my day. Ah. And Ben is like a beanie animal and all squishy. Ha. His face when he laughs is like no other...I'll have to get those photos later.
So. I almost started to cry when I heard about three people in Wisconsin who died.

If you want this under a cut. Holler. Going along with the theme and others... +Being able to know my Grandma for 15 of her 71 years +My slippers, that I hope are never lost +My parent's divorce +Grandma Marlene and her immense amounts of awesomeness +Having PopPop point to his cheek for kisses +My mother's allowance of independence +Grandpa and Grandma B for giving us 80% of the things in our house +Countless trips to Seattle where you're reminded of greatness +Travel.travel.travel. +iPods. +Common sense +Pain pills. For which I can't fathom where I would be without. +Being friends with Samantha Jayne +Knowing Adam Nuno +My Grandma's car +Kendra Makela. For whom I've shared wonderful experiences with +Knowing Johan +Dan McDowell. Truly and completely. +Matt McDowell. +Chris McDowell. Mmm. I haven't updated on a day in quite a long time, but yesterday was an extremely enjoyable one. At 330. I went with Jennifer and Amy and Danielle to Los Altos. After some time went by...Jennifer and I ended up roaming Main Street. First old Jemima, age 80, came up to us and asked, "The hors d'oeuvres! Have you seen them? They're all supposed to be passing them out" And we replied confusedly, "No, we don't even know about any hors d'oeuvres" After walking around for some time, we ran into Jemima again and she recommended a place with fantastic chocolates and cookies. There, we met Rufus who assumed we were lovers. We found a book, 'Cooking in the Nude: Just Married' and decided it was a must-purchase for a later date in time. Rufus was a little slow, and responded with, "The way you guys talk embarrases me!" And Jennifer went on about how she was upset about gay marriage being illegal. She also inquired about the grapes on the wall, and Rufus told her all about how you can get them at Michael's. We learned how strong the coffay was and he was amused by me saying 'a smidge of cream.' We had to leave him though, and said later and we'd be back hopefully, to finish off some more greater than great cookies and chocolates. As we proceeded further down the street...and ate food at the Optometry place...and Sylvia let us take pictures of her display...and got cheese at Treasures, as well as some wonderful fruit beads, we ended up at Winona's. Blonde hair and a nice European accent. "Is this wine or cider?" I asked her. "Wiiiine...(sadface)" she replied. "Ouch. That's depressing" "Ya...you have to be 21" "Ya I'm trying to hold back anyway. So whatev." Then Jennifer replied something with an s sound. Winona thought we said "Turning 21 on Saturday" and got super excited and sang and danced to 'Turning 21 on Saturday! Turning 21 on Saturday!' behind the counter as we walked out and around the store. There we met up with Jemima again. And she asked us if we had any more recommendations. We said no, because we only went to where she recommended, and the rest was all wine if she liked it. She said that she wasn't really into it. And her husband (Standing nearby, eating cheese and not hearing very well) used to drink too heavily and it has affected his memory, and they were going to have some tests done. She told us to not drink, and tell all our friends the same. Her life story was told in less than a minute, and she even did that gentle wrist-touching maneuver as she was finishing. Jennifer and I both almost said 'Bye Jemima!' I will miss her. Later we saw Maritzio, and Roger who plays the violin with scraggly hair. And don't forget Laquisha. After Los Altos, we saw Amy's grandma who is fantastic. Next, we continued on to Shannon's house, where I beat Christopher up, and picked up Nicole and Shannon. Michelle couldn't contain her excitement, and I practiced hugging on her, Ian and Amber! who later sewed my purse in the middle of feeling our hip bones and dancing to cell phone tunes. Kendra was there and I touched her 'sensational ass' before I caught up with Mexican, as she filled me in on some things. Erica F is always enjoyable, and there were the likes of Kelly G, Derek (Who suggested I knew him from 8th grade ASB) Alex P and some others. After the football kids obtained the MVAL champion status, we went to In N Out where Ryan Berry and all sorts of other fellows were. There was even a man in the parking lot who didn't care that the door to his trailer-less semi-truck wasn't closed, and gave us the thumbs up as he walked away that we could get in. We climbed into the cab, and took dark cell phone pictures, before leaving for 'The Chill Spot' which required us going over a ginormous bridge over marshland West of 880 that I have strangely never been on. It was fairly exciting. I also realized that I used to go to 'The Chill Spot' with my Dad and brothers when we lived in the apartment and we'd walk on the levees and go fishing. And then we came home. Oh joy!

A few days ago, I was sitting on the brick driveway of my grandparent's house, overseeing the records book for the estate sale.

Along came an old man on a raggedy grey bicycle. His worn pants were tucked into his worn socks, which were placed in his frayed shoes. After purchasing his fifty cent roll of tape, he placed it in his tattered backpack, choosing not to put it in his grocery bags which hung on the handlebars. His pockets were already overflowing as well. Before his departure, he put on a round skateboarding helmet and gardening gloves, and retrieved his bicycle from the dirt. Through the gates and down the street he went, to the rest of the sales in Los Altos, his habitual Saturday activity.

If and when I get old, I hope I'm as gangster as that old man. And if not, then I want to enjoy five porch years, before become an actual gangster in sweat suits who participates in drive-by's in the ghetto for those who mug a nigga.

Mind you. 
This is a school assignment.
I detest poetry.

I'm told to write down
my adjective

So I think
and think
very adamantly

And ponder
if I should write down the whole truth
because I have an answer in my head

I have ma mere
Lenient and gentle
Who remembers that strict rules 
don't usually promote good character
and plans often change

I have two grandmas
One with squishy hugs and a smoker's laugh
The other with sophistication
who shares my interest in aesthetics

I have three brothers
who turned me off
to lots of frilly things
One who is successful and outgoing
smart and cosmopolitan
which I strive to be

I have people who sing songs
and make for moments 
of enthusiasm
and active rhythmic movements

A family of coffee and cigarettes
with witty words
and talk of the world ending

I have all these things to remember
Thoughts and influences
and places

They tell me to write down
who I am
and I think 
very intently

if I should write down the whole truth
or what I can think of
because I have answers in my head

There's Seattle where I always go
Full of rain and independence
Plants and water and sleepiness

There's Thailand where the world is different
Where Malee is from
With spicy food 
Where age doesn't affect law
and everything is mashed and exciting

I have journals and books and lists
so the uncomprehensible
can be remembered

I have my original iPod for love
Soymilk and organic food for health
Kraut Bracht for Christmas
Coffee and pills for life

I have all of it
All that makes my self
But I stop

and lazily write down strange.
